         <abstract id="aspace_3fbdc5ed9276bb13a67dbc53be45710b">Sermons of Peter Starr, together with the sermons of his predecessor in Kent (now Warren), Connecticut, Sylvanus Osborn, and of two relatives by marriage, John Keep and John Stevens. Three-fourths of the papers are by Peter Starr. During the Revolutionary War Starr shifted his loyalty, and the sermons provide biblical justification on both sides. John Keep was a chaplain during the war and a number of his camp sermons are in the collection.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/nr2002016501"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Starr, Peter, 1744-1829</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
